*NVIDIA just rewired the AI stack at CES 2026.* 

What took enterprise teams months now deploys in a weekend. Physical AI is no longer experimental — it’s shipping in production vehicles, robots trained entirely in simulation, and agentic AI systems operating without step-by-step instruction.

* The biggest shift:*  context memory is no longer the bottleneck. AI systems can now retain full decision histories locally. The constraint has moved from memory to agency.

* CES 2026 highlights from NVIDIA:* 
• Level 3 autonomy scaling globally by 2026
• Multi-model agent routing replacing monolithic stacks
• Open-source foundation models enabling national and industry AI
• Agentic systems planning and executing end-to-end

Hundreds of billions are already in motion. The companies moving now will define the next decade of industrial AI.
